Cooking the chicken for our “Chicken Club” sandwich. Slow poached Baffoni Farm chicken in bacon fat, white wine & rosemary. So tender, so flavorful. On our house baked white (which is a pain de mie style bread with some of our sour dough starter & about 10% whole wheat), black pepper aioli, smoked bacon, lettuce & preserved roasted red peppers. It’s an homage & trip down memory lane for me from when I was little. Once in a while my mom had to go see my father and pick up his check on Friday at Sears on North Main Street, and if we were lucky we would get to go across the street to Gregg’s and have lunch and see my aunt who was waitressing there. My favorite thing to get was always the club. Bacon, mayo & meat, lettuce, tomato, on toasted bread. It was so good, I can still taste the memories. 
Our riff is a little different, but I hope you like it. #food is #love ❤️

We turned 21 today! It was a busy day, a good day. 

Man, life moves so fast. It’s hard to take the time to stop and think when everything is in such constant motion.

So much life has taken place. 21 years. We’re old enough to drink! 

At some point I’d love to throw a party to celebrate still being here. But for now I’d just like to tell everyone how much they mean to me and how thankful I am to have had and have so many incredible people in my life, our teams, our guests, our farmers, friends, family and our community. We’ve been through a lot together, especially these past few years, and I am so very thankful to all of you for being here and for being such an important part of our life. So much love and gratitude. 

Cheers and thank you, XO Derek

One of my favorite things to make has always been soup. There’s just something about one pot meals that are as spiritually fulfilling as they are physically. Building something layer by layer, over hours, simmering, seasoning, standing over the pot waiting for the ingredients to come together and for T hat moment when it all catalyzes into something special. It goes beyond just being delicious. Soup just makes you feel good. It reminds me of where I’ve come from, why I cook, and it can help center me when I’m feeling down, stressed, or overwhelmed. It’s the reason I’ve had them on the menus opening day 21 years ago, and every day since. The first week we were opened, I had no money for advertising (and barely enough to open), and I would make quarts of soup and grilled bread and send Steve up and down the street and through the city, dropping them off at different businesses, just to say hi and introduce ourselves. I thought what better way to say hello than with a warm bowl of soup. 
If they can taste how much we care, then maybe they will come and see us. In honor of those first few days, in the spirit of trying to give back more than we take, and to shine a light on the staggering amount of food insecurity that still exists today here in Rhode Island (and beyond), for the entire month of March we are donating 21% of all soup sales to the Rhode Island Community Food Bank. I hope that you can help us support them serving their vital mission and critical work. It is so important. Everyone needs a warm, nutritious meal. Many people depend on their programs to help feed their families. If you are able, please donate $21 to the RI Community Food Bank this month. Thank you for all your support over the years, and thank you for caring. No act of kindness and good will is insignificant. ❤️ XO dw

Loving our new mural from my good friend, the very talented Mr. Shawn Gilheeney of @providencepaintedsigns. We’ve been having some big challenges with vandalism & graffiti in our neighborhood and I thought we’d just try to turn it into something positive & beautiful instead. 

We wanted to do something that felt like it paid homage to the history of the neighborhood, inspirations for our cooking, and to my late grandfather Joe Piti who passed away earlier this year, so we wrote the words in Italian. Today would have been my grandfather’s birthday, so it felt fitting to post this today. Hope you like it gramps. ❤️

And thank you Shawn for continuing to make our city a little more special & beautiful with your art & craft. 🙏

You can enjoy it vegetarian or add an over easy egg, a piece of roasted fish, roasted chicken or grilled steak, whatever your feeling. Here it is with herb roasted Black Bass. Love polenta!

Nick’s on Broadway - Tasting Menu - had an amazing meal at Nick’s on Broadway in Providence last Saturday!! Derek Wagner, who I have known for at least 20 years has done an amazing job with his restaurant and involvement with sourcing local. He supports local in every way possible and is so true to Rhode Island. The menu that was put together for me was extraordinary, from presentation to the delectable flavors of each ingredient.  What a treat to be able to visit with Derek and enjoy his food!! If you are ever in Rhode Island, you must have a meal at his restaurant!  Ciao for now!

Just a beautiful salad leaving the pass. We love salads. Bright, vibrant, crisp, fresh, delicious. This one is our Pea Green & Kale Salad, Caesar style. @allenfarmsorganics pea greens, @schartnerfarms kale, carrots, tomatoes, beets & @wardsberryfarm radishes, with our anchovy dressing, crispy croutons, pecorino romano & a whole lotta love.  #supoortyourlocalfarmers
Building those layers. Pulling out all the flavors. It’s great soup weather! And I #Love #Soup!

Warm pumpkin bread pudding with pumpkin-caramel-white chocolate chip ice cream & caramel. So good! Made with @schartnerfarms pumpkin.

📸 @antoinettebruno
Cutting those gorgeous dry aged @blackbirdfarmri beef rib eyes for service this weekend! #supportyourlocalfarmers

It’s perfect weather for our Hot Drinks Menu! Inside or outside cozied up by the fireplaces or To Go! Hot Chocolate, Chai, Hot Cider, Teas & Coffee drinks, all available deliciously spiked with your favorite spirits. Did you know that we make our own special spice blends for our house chai & hot chocolate and all our tea blends are sourced from @farmacyherbs? Did you also know that you can add a scoop of vanilla or pumpkin ice cream to your hot drinks!?! Also… our HOUSE EGGNOG RETURNS THIS WEEK!!!!

Cutting some beautiful Bavette steaks for this weekend! 

@blackbirdfarmri #beef #supportyourlocalfarmers
Cutting some beautiful RI landed fluke, one of my favorites to break down. We’ve got some beautiful Tautog too! #supportyourlocalfishermen #fresh #fish!

Our house Eggnog is back for the season! Made with farm fresh @baffonispoultryfarm eggs. Spiked with Cognac or not, it’s delicious! Available in quarts To Go too!  Limited quantities, so get some while it lasts! 

Great 📸 @nealrpandozzi ❤️

Wishing everyone peace, love, good health & happiness from our family to yours, Happy Thanksgiving. ❤️

We’ll be open Friday morning starting at 10am, last seating at 8pm. We’ll have our Eggs Benedict’s on! Stop by for brunch, lunch, dinner or cocktails & snacks. XO
Another beautiful batch of Cassoulet coming out of the oven! It’s a great day for a bowl of slow braised beans with Blackbird Farm pork, beef & Baffoni Farm chicken.

Sometimes you just need a good plate of breakfast. A couple of fresh over easy yolky @baffonispoultryfarm eggs, roasted @schartnerfarms potatoes, warm buttery buttermilk biscuit, a few strips of smokey New England bacon, @allenfarmsorganics pea greens. 

Though it’s evolved a lot over the years, The Special Plus has been a staple on our breakfast/brunch menu since opening, an an homage to our original space that was an old diner for many, many years. Available all day until 3pm, Wednesday-Sunday since 2002. XO ❤️ 

📸 @______c.j
Wild New England mussels! Special this weekend, with roasted squash, tomatillo, chili, parsley-butter broth. Served with some aioli slathered focaccia for the win.

Steak & Eggs is back on the menu today! A beautiful new side of beef arrived this week from @blackbirdfarmri and our first cuts will be a mixed grill of bavette & flank. Slathered in our special  chipotle sauce and served with a couple of @baffonispoultryfarm eggs nice & runny, roasted @schartnerfarms potatoes, toasted buttery buttermilk biscuit, and a little @allenfarmsorganics pea greens. XO #beef
It’s a great day to chill on the covered patio, sit by the fires, listen to the rain & crush some oysters & rosé!!! #brunch ❤️XO
Cutting some beautiful @blackbirdfarmri beef sirloin steaks! #beef

Stunning Day Boat Sea Scallops in for crudo this weekend from our friends & fishermen @narragansett_bay_lobsters! So sweet. So fresh. #doit

HAPPY NEW YEAR! 
From our family to yours. Thank you from the bottom of our hearts to our entire @nicksonbroadway family, friends, guests, partners, community and team members for all the love & support this year. We appreciate you and we love you so very much. This past year was filled with so many beautiful moments, smiles, laughter and wonderful people that make all the hard work, difficult times and long hours seem so worth it. So much going on in the world today, and we are praying for love and compassion and peace for all. We are looking forward to 2024 with big open hearts, and hopeful wonder.

After an amazing New Year’s Eve Celebration (thank you!) we are taking the week off to give the entire team time to rest, recharge & spend time with their loved ones. WE ARE CLOSED THIS WEEK! 
See you next week! XO ❤️🙏
